Quote:  MOUSE-EARED CHICKWEED (<i>Cerastium [glomeratum]</i>) [which is sometimes] often called mouse-ear for short, is found in cultivated fields and thin pastures throughout both islands. ... The leaves are downy, [pale yellowing-green] and oval (whence the name `mouse ear'), ...
